== Literature Review

This literature review synthesizes existing research on the intersection of humanitarianism and development work, decolonial theory, and philosophical inquiries of knowledge. The review is structured around three main themes: (1) the historical and contemporary dynamics of humanitarianism and development work, (2) the principles and critiques of decolonial theory, and (3) the philosophical underpinnings of knowledge production in these fields.
